            <h2>Culture</h2>
            <p>The culture of Uganda is diverse, with over 50 ethnic groups, each with its own unique traditions, music, and dance. Ugandans are known for their hospitality, and cultural ceremonies and dances play an important role in community life. The traditional dress for many Ugandans consists of colorful fabrics, and the most popular dance forms include the Bakisimba and the Ekizino.</p>
